modules.description: Converts event data into S-expression format, using a provided function to serialize the address type. Works with persistent connection event structures that include an address and error information. Used to serialize event logs for debugging or persistence.

Serializes event data into S-expressions using a custom address serializer, handling persistent connection events with address and error fields. Supports debugging and logging by converting structured event data into a readable format. Operations include transforming event records and embedding error details within the serialized output. Example uses include generating log entries or storing event states for later retrieval.

Handles HTTP and HTTPS connections, including TLS negotiation and persistent TCP sessions. Operates on URL strings, socket descriptors, and SSL contexts. Enables server-side listening with SSL support and maintains long-lived client connections.

Encodes event data into S-expressions with custom address serialization, capturing connection states and errors. It includes functions to transform event records and embed detailed error information. This enables generation of structured log entries or persistent storage of event metadata. Examples include logging connection failures or reconstructing event states from serialized data.
